('02f2d04e-7349-449f-b4e1-6fcce09b891d', '6ce8cf6f-e9bd-42b5-9cc6-bda9fe1f1e05', '5', 24, 21, 5, 95, '{\"5_q1\":\"a) when traffic is heavy\",\"5_q10\":\"d) none of the answers is correct\",\"5_q11\":\"d) none of the answers is correct\",\"5_q12\":\"d) all answers are correct\",\"5_q13\":\"d) none of the answers is correct\",\"5_q14\":\"d) none of the answers is correct\",\"5_q15\":\"c) white and blue\",\"5_q16\":\"c) it can also have belts on rear seats\",\"5_q17\":\"c) minister of defense\",\"5_q18\":\"d) none of the answers is correct\",\"5_q19\":\"d) none of the answers is correct\",\"5_q2\":\"d) the front lights are orange\",\"5_q20\":\"d) none of the answers is correct\",\"5_q21\":\"a) baby cars\",\"5_q3\":\"a) priority vehicles\",\"5_q4\":\"c) blue\",\"5_q5\":\"d) red\",\"5_q6\":\"c) motor vehicle\",\"5_q7\":\"a) one or many white lights\",\"5_q8\":\"d) none of the answers is correct\",\"5_q9\":\"d) 200m\"}', 0, '2025-09-25 13:39:39', 0, '2025-09-25 13:39:39', '2025-09-25 13:39:39', '[{\"questionId\":\"5_q1\",\"questionText\":\"Out of agglomerations, a driver of a car or a set of cars of which the maximum authorized weight exceeds 3.500kg or of which the overall length exceeds 10m must, except when it overtakes or gets ready to overtake another vehicle, leave between his car and that which proceeds him a sufficient interval to permit vehicles which overtake it to cut in without danger in case of necessity. But this provision is however not applicable when:\",\"options\":{\"a\":\"a) when traffic is heavy\",\"b\":\"b) on the position of the public way overtaking is forbidden\",\"c\":\"c) A and B are correct answers\",\"d\":\"d) none of the answers is correct\"},\"userAnswer\":\"a) when traffic is heavy\",\"userAnswerLetter\":\"a\",\"correctAnswer\":\"c) A and B are correct answers\",\"correctAnswerLetter\":\"c\",\"isCorrect\":false,\"points\":0,\"questionImgUrl\":null},{\"questionId\":\"5_q10\",\"questionText\":\"Except on highways and roads for automobiles, the section of the roadway situated beyond a wide and continuous white line drawn on the roadway to indicate its fictitious border, is reserved for:\",\"options\":{\"a\":\"a) stopping only\",\"b\":\"b) parking only\",\"c\":\"c) stopping and parking\",\"d\":\"d) none of the answers is correct\"},\"userAnswer\":\"d) none of the answers is correct\",\"userAnswerLetter\":\"d\",\"correctAnswer\":\"c) stopping and parking\",\"correctAnswerLetter\":\"c\",\"isCorrect\":false,\"points\":0,\"questionImgUrl\":null},{\"questionId\":\"5_q11\",\"questionText\":\"Provisional marks constituted by orange colored studs may replace the following lines:\",\"options\":{\"a\":\"a) continuous white lines\",\"b\":\"b) continuous and broken longitudinal white lines\",\"c\":\"c) the parallels continuous and broken longitudinal lines\",\"d\":\"d) none of the answers is correct\"},\"userAnswer\":\"d) none of the answers is correct\",\"userAnswerLetter\":\"d\",\"correctAnswer\":\"b) continuous and broken longitudinal white lines\",\"correctAnswerLetter\":\"b\",\"isCorrect\":false,\"points\":0,\"questionImgUrl\":null},{\"questionId\":\"5_q12\",\"questionText\":\"When it is not possible to see distinctly up to a distance of 200m, the presence on the public way, the animal pulled vehicles, hand carts, load or saddle animals and cattle must be signaled in the following way:\",\"options\":{\"a\":\"a) in front, by a white light\",\"b\":\"b) in front, by a yellow or orange light\",\"c\":\"c) at the back, by red light\",\"d\":\"d) all answers are correct\"},\"userAnswer\":\"d) all answers are correct\",\"userAnswerLetter\":\"d\",\"correctAnswer\":\"d) all answers are correct\",\"correctAnswerLetter\":\"d\",\"isCorrect\":true,\"points\":1,\"questionImgUrl\":null},{\"questionId\":\"5_q13\",\"questionText\":\"Except local regulation or particular lay-out of the areas, every vehicle at stop or in parking, in case it is on pavement used by pedestrians, the driver must leave them at least a space of the following measures to allow their passage without moving onto the roadway:\",\"options\":{\"a\":\"a) one meter wide band\",\"b\":\"b) two meters wide band\",\"c\":\"c) 0.50 meter wide band\",\"d\":\"d) none of the answers is correct\"},\"userAnswer\":\"d) none of the answers is correct\",\"userAnswerLetter\":\"d\",\"correctAnswer\":\"a) one meter wide band\",\"correctAnswerLetter\":\"a\",\"isCorrect\":false,\"points\":0,\"questionImgUrl\":null},{\"questionId\":\"5_q14\",\"questionText\":\"The signal showing the place which is specifically reserved as a parking place for public transport is characterized by a surface of this color:\",\"options\":{\"a\":\"a) blue\",\"b\":\"b) white\",\"c\":\"c) red\",\"d\":\"d) none of the answers is correct\"},\"userAnswer\":\"d) none of the answers is correct\",\"userAnswerLetter\":\"d\",\"correctAnswer\":\"d) none of the answers is correct\",\"correctAnswerLetter\":\"d\",\"isCorrect\":true,\"points\":1,\"questionImgUrl\":null},{\"questionId\":\"5_q15\",\"questionText\":\"The signal showing that the road, at the entrance of which it is placed, leads to a dead end is characterized by symbols of following colors:\",\"options\":{\"a\":\"a) black and red\",\"b\":\"b) black and white\",\"c\":\"c) white and blue\",\"d\":\"d) none of the answers is correct\"},\"userAnswer\":\"c) white and blue\",\"userAnswerLetter\":\"c\",\"correctAnswer\":\"c) white and blue\",\"correctAnswerLetter\":\"c\",\"isCorrect\":true,\"points\":1,\"questionImgUrl\":null},{\"questionId\":\"5_q16\",\"questionText\":\"Every motor vehicle assigned to transport people of which the maximum number of the occupants is below six, including the driver must be endowed with security belts for the following persons:\",\"options\":{\"a\":\"a) the driver\",\"b\":\"b) the passenger occupying the front seat\",\"c\":\"c) it can also have belts on rear seats\",\"d\":\"d) all answers are correct\"},\"userAnswer\":\"c) it can also have belts on rear seats\",\"userAnswerLetter\":\"c\",\"correctAnswer\":\"d) all answers are correct\",\"correctAnswerLetter\":\"d\",\"isCorrect\":false,\"points\":0,\"questionImgUrl\":null},{\"questionId\":\"5_q17\",\"questionText\":\"Except to armed forces vehicles, a motor vehicle with armor or any other device permitting to be used in aggression or defense cannot move on the public way without special permission. This permission is authorized by:\",\"options\":{\"a\":\"a) the minister entrusted with transport or his delegate\",\"b\":\"b) National Police\",\"c\":\"c) minister of defense\",\"d\":\"d) tax department\"},\"userAnswer\":\"c) minister of defense\",\"userAnswerLetter\":\"c\",\"correctAnswer\":\"a) the minister entrusted with transport or his delegate\",\"correctAnswerLetter\":\"a\",\"isCorrect\":false,\"points\":0,\"questionImgUrl\":null},{\"questionId\":\"5_q18\",\"questionText\":\"Between twilight and daybreak, where a herd comprises more than four heads of cattle or more than six of small animals, it will be signaled by:\",\"options\":{\"a\":\"a) white light hand lamp or orange hand lamp borne in front of herd\",\"b\":\"b) a red light hand lamp or yellow light hand lamp borne at the back of the herd\",\"c\":\"c) A and B are both correct\",\"d\":\"d) none of the answers is correct\"},\"userAnswer\":\"d) none of the answers is correct\",\"userAnswerLetter\":\"d\",\"correctAnswer\":\"d) none of the answers is correct\",\"correctAnswerLetter\":\"d\",\"isCorrect\":true,\"points\":1,\"questionImgUrl\":null},{\"questionId\":\"5_q19\",\"questionText\":\"A convoy cannot occupy a distance of more than 500m. When this occurs, it must be divided into groups of vehicles occupying the way or a distance of a maximum 50m. however these provisions are not applicable to:\",\"options\":{\"a\":\"a) vehicle of Rwanda national police\",\"b\":\"b) Military vehicles forming a convoy in built-up areas\",\"c\":\"c) A and B are both correct\",\"d\":\"d) none of the answers is correct\"},\"userAnswer\":\"d) none of the answers is correct\",\"userAnswerLetter\":\"d\",\"correctAnswer\":\"b) Military vehicles forming a convoy in built-up areas\",\"correctAnswerLetter\":\"b\",\"isCorrect\":false,\"points\":0,\"questionImgUrl\":null},{\"questionId\":\"5_q2\",\"questionText\":\"The direction indicating lights must be constituted by fixed systems with flashing light disposed in pairs at the back and the front faces of the vehicle. These lights are characterized by these colors:\",\"options\":{\"a\":\"a) the front lights are white or yellow\",\"b\":\"b) the back lights are red or orange\",\"c\":\"c) A and B are both correct\",\"d\":\"d) the front lights are orange\"},\"userAnswer\":\"d) the front lights are orange\",\"userAnswerLetter\":\"d\",\"correctAnswer\":\"c) A and B are both correct\",\"correctAnswerLetter\":\"c\",\"isCorrect\":false,\"points\":0,\"questionImgUrl\":null},{\"questionId\":\"5_q20\",\"questionText\":\"When a second vehicle is trailed by a yoked vehicle and that the length of the line overpasses 18m exclusive of the first vehicle shaft, they process the following:\",\"options\":{\"a\":\"a) the second vehicle must be accompanied by a conveyor\",\"b\":\"b) two conveyors\",\"c\":\"c) A and B are both correct\",\"d\":\"d) none of the answers is correct\"},\"userAnswer\":\"d) none of the answers is correct\",\"userAnswerLetter\":\"d\",\"correctAnswer\":\"a) the second vehicle must be accompanied by a conveyor\",\"correctAnswerLetter\":\"a\",\"isCorrect\":false,\"points\":0,\"questionImgUrl\":null},{\"questionId\":\"5_q21\",\"questionText\":\"The obligation to be equipped with a signaling system does not apply to the following vehicles:\",\"options\":{\"a\":\"a) baby cars\",\"b\":\"b) wheelchairs\",\"c\":\"c) A and B are both correct\",\"d\":\"d) none of the answers is correct\"},\"userAnswer\":\"a) baby cars\",\"userAnswerLetter\":\"a\",\"correctAnswer\":\"c) A and B are both correct\",\"correctAnswerLetter\":\"c\",\"isCorrect\":false,\"points\":0,\"questionImgUrl\":null},{\"questionId\":\"5_q3\",\"questionText\":\"The sounding alarms of motor vehicles must emit a uniform sound, continuous and not shrilling, but these vehicles may be provided with a special alarm which does not meet the requirements of this paragraph:\",\"options\":{\"a\":\"a) priority vehicles\",\"b\":\"b) vehicles assigned to road maintenance\",\"c\":\"c) the vehicles with the width exceed 2.10m\",\"d\":\"d) A and B are both correct\"},\"userAnswer\":\"a) priority vehicles\",\"userAnswerLetter\":\"a\",\"correctAnswer\":\"d) A and B are both correct\",\"correctAnswerLetter\":\"d\",\"isCorrect\":false,\"points\":0,\"questionImgUrl\":null},{\"questionId\":\"5_q4\",\"questionText\":\"The signal of no overtaking vehicles with an engine apart from those with two wheels without a sidecar has the symbols of these colors:\",\"options\":{\"a\":\"a) white and black\",\"b\":\"b) red and black\",\"c\":\"c) blue\",\"d\":\"d) A and B are both correct\"},\"userAnswer\":\"c) blue\",\"userAnswerLetter\":\"c\",\"correctAnswer\":\"b) red and black\",\"correctAnswerLetter\":\"b\",\"isCorrect\":false,\"points\":0,\"questionImgUrl\":null},{\"questionId\":\"5_q5\",\"questionText\":\"The signal prohibiting vehicular traffic from both directions is characterized by a surface of the following color:\",\"options\":{\"a\":\"a) black\",\"b\":\"b) white\",\"c\":\"c) blue\",\"d\":\"d) red\"},\"userAnswer\":\"d) red\",\"userAnswerLetter\":\"d\",\"correctAnswer\":\"b) white\",\"correctAnswerLetter\":\"b\",\"isCorrect\":false,\"points\":0,\"questionImgUrl\":null},{\"questionId\":\"5_q6\",\"questionText\":\"The vehicles mentioned hereafter must be equipped with a sounding alarm apparatus that can be heard at a distance of 20m:\",\"options\":{\"a\":\"a) motorcycle\",\"b\":\"b) moped\",\"c\":\"c) motor vehicle\",\"d\":\"d) none of the answers is correct\"},\"userAnswer\":\"c) motor vehicle\",\"userAnswerLetter\":\"c\",\"correctAnswer\":\"b) moped\",\"correctAnswerLetter\":\"b\",\"isCorrect\":false,\"points\":0,\"questionImgUrl\":null},{\"questionId\":\"5_q7\",\"questionText\":\"When it is not possible to see distinctly up to a distance of 200m, the formation of armed forces on march and of all other groups of pedestrians such as procession or school children groups in lines under the supervision of a school master, when they move on the roadway with more than one front, must be signaled by the white light held on the left side in front and red light held on the left side at the back but the sides of these units or groups must, where their length is superior to 6m, be signaled by:\",\"options\":{\"a\":\"a) one or many white lights\",\"b\":\"b) many yellow lights\",\"c\":\"c) many orange lights\",\"d\":\"d) All answers are correct\"},\"userAnswer\":\"a) one or many white lights\",\"userAnswerLetter\":\"a\",\"correctAnswer\":\"d) All answers are correct\",\"correctAnswerLetter\":\"d\",\"isCorrect\":false,\"points\":0,\"questionImgUrl\":null},{\"questionId\":\"5_q8\",\"questionText\":\"The front side lights and the back ones of motor vehicles with the length and the width which, load included, do not exceed, respectively 6 and 2 m and to which no other vehicle is yoked, can be replaced by parking lights when these vehicles, at stop or in parking in suburbs are parallel to the border of the roadway. Those lights must have the following colors:\",\"options\":{\"a\":\"a) white or yellow at the front side face\",\"b\":\"b) red or yellow at the back side face\",\"c\":\"c) A and B are both correct\",\"d\":\"d) none of the answers is correct\"},\"userAnswer\":\"d) none of the answers is correct\",\"userAnswerLetter\":\"d\",\"correctAnswer\":\"c) A and B are both correct\",\"correctAnswerLetter\":\"c\",\"isCorrect\":false,\"points\":0,\"questionImgUrl\":null},{\"questionId\":\"5_q9\",\"questionText\":\"Loading lights must be visible at night by fine weather by the driver of the vehicle being at least at:\",\"options\":{\"a\":\"a) 50m\",\"b\":\"b) 100m\",\"c\":\"c) 150m\",\"d\":\"d) 200m\"},\"userAnswer\":\"d) 200m\",\"userAnswerLetter\":\"d\",\"correctAnswer\":\"d) 200m\",\"correctAnswerLetter\":\"d\",\"isCorrect\":true,\"points\":1,\"questionImgUrl\":null}]'),
('51eb78b6-9150-4f01-b38d-3af055c53261', '6ce8cf6f-e9bd-42b5-9cc6-bda9fe1f1e05', '9', 40, 20, 8, 56, '{\"9_q1\":\"b) Agricultural vehicles when they are in traffic within a maximum radius of 25km\",\"9_q10\":\"a) 10 tones\",\"9_q11\":\"a) 70 km/h\",\"9_q12\":\"a) 20 km/h\",\"9_q13\":\"a) in front of entrances and exits of public passages\",\"9_q14\":\"a) in front by a yellow light held on the left side\",\"9_q15\":\"a) inside as well as outside built-up areas\",\"9_q16\":\"a) 3m\",\"9_q17\":\"a) 30cm\",\"9_q18\":\"c) 1.80m\",\"9_q19\":\"b) it must be at the back left edge of vehicle\",\"9_q2\":\"c) Pedestrians’ crossings\",\"9_q20\":\"b) 30cm\",\"9_q3\":\"c) 7 years\",\"9_q4\":\"a) 2weeks\",\"9_q5\":\"c) A and B are the correct answers\",\"9_q6\":\"c) red\",\"9_q7\":\"a) 50m\",\"9_q8\":\"a) a red piece of cloth measuring a minimum 0.50m by side\",\"9_q9\":\"a) 12 tones\"}', 0, '2025-09-27 17:53:26', 0, '2025-09-27 17:53:26', '2025-09-27 17:53:26', '[{\"questionId\":\"9_q1\",\"questionText\":\"It is forbidden the circulation of self-propelling vehicles and trailers pulled by these vehicles, when their wheels are provided with either rigid bandages or elastic bandages of less than 0.04 meter thick. But these provisions do not apply on the following vehicles:\",\"options\":{\"a\":\"a) Military vehicles\",\"b\":\"b) Agricultural vehicles when they are in traffic within a maximum radius of 25km\",\"c\":\"c) the vehicles of national police\",\"d\":\"d) no correct answer\"},\"userAnswer\":\"b) Agricultural vehicles when they are in traffic within a maximum radius of 25km\",\"userAnswerLetter\":\"b\",\"correctAnswer\":\"b) Agricultural vehicles when they are in traffic within a maximum radius of 25km\",\"correctAnswerLetter\":\"b\",\"isCorrect\":true,\"points\":1,\"questionImgUrl\":\"\"},{\"questionId\":\"9_q10\",\"questionText\":\"Except in urban arrears, on the other roads as determined by the minister having transport in his duties, the maximum weight authorized for three and more axle vehicles excepting semi-trailers is:\",\"options\":{\"a\":\"a) 10 tones\",\"b\":\"b) 12 tones\",\"c\":\"c) 15 tones\",\"d\":\"d) none of the answers is correct\"},\"userAnswer\":\"a) 10 tones\",\"userAnswerLetter\":\"a\",\"correctAnswer\":\"d) none of the answers is correct\",\"correctAnswerLetter\":\"d\",\"isCorrect\":false,\"points\":0,\"questionImgUrl\":\"\"},{\"questionId\":\"9_q11\",\"questionText\":\"In absence of more restrictive regulations, maximum speed for vehicles which by design have no suspension is :\",\"options\":{\"a\":\"a) 70 km/h\",\"b\":\"b) 40 km/h\",\"c\":\"c) 25 km/h\",\"d\":\"d) 20 km/h\"},\"userAnswer\":\"a) 70 km/h\",\"userAnswerLetter\":\"a\",\"correctAnswer\":\"c) 25 km/h\",\"correctAnswerLetter\":\"c\",\"isCorrect\":false,\"points\":0,\"questionImgUrl\":\"\"},{\"questionId\":\"9_q12\",\"questionText\":\"In absence of more restrictive regulations, maximum speed for vehicles which by decision have no suspension is :\",\"options\":{\"a\":\"a) 20 km/h\",\"b\":\"b) 40 km/h\",\"c\":\"c) 35 km/h\",\"d\":\"d) none of the answers is correct\"},\"userAnswer\":\"a) 20 km/h\",\"userAnswerLetter\":\"a\",\"correctAnswer\":\"d) none of the answers is correct\",\"correctAnswerLetter\":\"d\",\"isCorrect\":false,\"points\":0,\"questionImgUrl\":\"\"},{\"questionId\":\"9_q13\",\"questionText\":\"On these spaces, parking a vehicle is forbidden:\",\"options\":{\"a\":\"a) in front of entrances and exits of public passages\",\"b\":\"b) on the roadway at places where it is divided into traffic bands materialized by non-continuous marks\",\"c\":\"c) A and B are both correct\",\"d\":\"d) none of the answers is correct\"},\"userAnswer\":\"a) in front of entrances and exits of public passages\",\"userAnswerLetter\":\"a\",\"correctAnswer\":\"a) in front of entrances and exits of public passages\",\"correctAnswerLetter\":\"a\",\"isCorrect\":true,\"points\":1,\"questionImgUrl\":\"\"},{\"questionId\":\"9_q14\",\"questionText\":\"Between twilight and daybreak or because of circumstances such as fog or heavy rain it is not possible to see distinctly up to distance of 200m, the presence on the public way of groups of pedestrians such as processions or school children groups in line under the supervision of a school master, when they move on the road way with more than one front person, must be signaled in the following way:\",\"options\":{\"a\":\"a) in front by a yellow light held on the left side\",\"b\":\"b) at the back by a red light held on the left side, by the individual in the nearest position to the axis of the roadway\",\"c\":\"c) A and B are correct\",\"d\":\"d) none of the answers is correct\"},\"userAnswer\":\"a) in front by a yellow light held on the left side\",\"userAnswerLetter\":\"a\",\"correctAnswer\":\"b) at the back by a red light held on the left side, by the individual in the nearest position to the axis of the roadway\",\"correctAnswerLetter\":\"b\",\"isCorrect\":false,\"points\":0,\"questionImgUrl\":\"\"},{\"questionId\":\"9_q15\",\"questionText\":\"Luminous warning signs are authorized for warning a driver that he is going to be overtaken. They are used in the following areas:\",\"options\":{\"a\":\"a) inside as well as outside built-up areas\",\"b\":\"b) approaching the mounted animals only\",\"c\":\"c) approaching only livestock\",\"d\":\"d) none of the answers is correct\"},\"userAnswer\":\"a) inside as well as outside built-up areas\",\"userAnswerLetter\":\"a\",\"correctAnswer\":\"a) inside as well as outside built-up areas\",\"correctAnswerLetter\":\"a\",\"isCorrect\":true,\"points\":1,\"questionImgUrl\":\"\"},{\"questionId\":\"9_q16\",\"questionText\":\"The vehicles with the width which is superior to the following measures must be provided with loading light:\",\"options\":{\"a\":\"a) 3m\",\"b\":\"b) 2.50m\",\"c\":\"c) 1.10m\",\"d\":\"d) none of the answers is correct\"},\"userAnswer\":\"a) 3m\",\"userAnswerLetter\":\"a\",\"correctAnswer\":\"d) none of the answers is correct\",\"correctAnswerLetter\":\"d\",\"isCorrect\":false,\"points\":0,\"questionImgUrl\":\"\"},{\"questionId\":\"9_q17\",\"questionText\":\"No light or reflector can be placed in such a manner that the lowest point of its lighting surface be below the following measures from the ground level, the vehicle being empt:\",\"options\":{\"a\":\"a) 30cm\",\"b\":\"b) 20 cm\",\"c\":\"c) 50cm\",\"d\":\"d) none of the answers is correct\"},\"userAnswer\":\"a) 30cm\",\"userAnswerLetter\":\"a\",\"correctAnswer\":\"d) none of the answers is correct\",\"correctAnswerLetter\":\"d\",\"isCorrect\":false,\"points\":0,\"questionImgUrl\":\"\"},{\"questionId\":\"9_q18\",\"questionText\":\"For an empty vehicle, the highest point of the illuminating area of the front and back position lights cannot be at more than the following measurements above the ground:\",\"options\":{\"a\":\"a) 1.50m\",\"b\":\"b) 1.75m\",\"c\":\"c) 1.80m\",\"d\":\"d) none of the answers is correct\"},\"userAnswer\":\"c) 1.80m\",\"userAnswerLetter\":\"c\",\"correctAnswer\":\"d) none of the answers is correct\",\"correctAnswerLetter\":\"d\",\"isCorrect\":false,\"points\":0,\"questionImgUrl\":\"\"},{\"questionId\":\"9_q19\",\"questionText\":\"Every motor vehicle or trailer pulled by such a vehicle shall be provided with a green light permitting the driver to signal that he has noticed the warning of the person who is ready to overtake him. This light must be placed as follows:\",\"options\":{\"a\":\"a) it must be fixed nearest to the left border of vehicle\",\"b\":\"b) it must be at the back left edge of vehicle\",\"c\":\"c) it must be fixed at the back nearest the right\",\"d\":\"d) none of the answers is correct\"},\"userAnswer\":\"b) it must be at the back left edge of vehicle\",\"userAnswerLetter\":\"b\",\"correctAnswer\":\"b) it must be at the back left edge of vehicle\",\"correctAnswerLetter\":\"b\",\"isCorrect\":true,\"points\":1,\"questionImgUrl\":\"\"},{\"questionId\":\"9_q2\",\"questionText\":\"The white lines parallel to the roadway are used by:\",\"options\":{\"a\":\"a) bicycles and mopeds\",\"b\":\"b) the barrows and cycles\",\"c\":\"c) Pedestrians’ crossings\",\"d\":\"d) None of the answers is correct.\"},\"userAnswer\":\"c) Pedestrians’ crossings\",\"userAnswerLetter\":\"c\",\"correctAnswer\":\"c) Pedestrians’ crossings\",\"correctAnswerLetter\":\"c\",\"isCorrect\":true,\"points\":1,\"questionImgUrl\":\"\"},{\"questionId\":\"9_q20\",\"questionText\":\"The width of the loading on motorcycles with a side car and trailer pulled by this cannot exceed the following measures of width of the vehicle when not loaded:\",\"options\":{\"a\":\"a) 1.25m\",\"b\":\"b) 30cm\",\"c\":\"c) 75cm\",\"d\":\"d) none of the answers is correct\"},\"userAnswer\":\"b) 30cm\",\"userAnswerLetter\":\"b\",\"correctAnswer\":\"b) 30cm\",\"correctAnswerLetter\":\"b\",\"isCorrect\":true,\"points\":1,\"questionImgUrl\":\"\"},{\"questionId\":\"9_q3\",\"questionText\":\"When the other seats are available in the car, it is forbidden to carry on the front seat the children of less than the following age:\",\"options\":{\"a\":\"a) 10 years\",\"b\":\"b) 12 years\",\"c\":\"c) 7 years\",\"d\":\"d) no correct answer\"},\"userAnswer\":\"c) 7 years\",\"userAnswerLetter\":\"c\",\"correctAnswer\":\"b) 12 years\",\"correctAnswerLetter\":\"b\",\"isCorrect\":false,\"points\":0,\"questionImgUrl\":\"\"},{\"questionId\":\"9_q4\",\"questionText\":\"In case of definitive out of use or definitive export of vehicle, the registration plates must be removed and sent back to the tax department service, this operation must be done in a period of:\",\"options\":{\"a\":\"a) 2weeks\",\"b\":\"b) 2months\",\"c\":\"c) 1month\",\"d\":\"d) there is no correct answer\"},\"userAnswer\":\"a) 2weeks\",\"userAnswerLetter\":\"a\",\"correctAnswer\":\"b) 2months\",\"correctAnswerLetter\":\"b\",\"isCorrect\":false,\"points\":0,\"questionImgUrl\":\"\"},{\"questionId\":\"9_q5\",\"questionText\":\"Borders of the public highway or the roadway must be signaled by reflectors, these devices must be so set up to let users see these for the following manner:\",\"options\":{\"a\":\"a) they see on their left the white reflectors only\",\"b\":\"b) on their right they see only the red or orange reflectors\",\"c\":\"c) A and B are the correct answers\",\"d\":\"d) none of the answers is correct\"},\"userAnswer\":\"c) A and B are the correct answers\",\"userAnswerLetter\":\"c\",\"correctAnswer\":\"c) A and B are the correct answers\",\"correctAnswerLetter\":\"c\",\"isCorrect\":true,\"points\":1,\"questionImgUrl\":\"\"},{\"questionId\":\"9_q6\",\"questionText\":\"Where traffic deviation is required, it is signaled at the beginning and all the way long by means of an indication signal:\",\"options\":{\"a\":\"a) black\",\"b\":\"b) white\",\"c\":\"c) red\",\"d\":\"d) none of the answers is correct\"},\"userAnswer\":\"c) red\",\"userAnswerLetter\":\"c\",\"correctAnswer\":\"d) none of the answers is correct\",\"correctAnswerLetter\":\"d\",\"isCorrect\":false,\"points\":0,\"questionImgUrl\":\"\"},{\"questionId\":\"9_q7\",\"questionText\":\"On the roads designated by the Minister having public way in his remit, the danger signals and indication signals must be made visible between night fall and day break by means either of special lighting or reflecting products. When the weather is clear visibility distance must be at least:\",\"options\":{\"a\":\"a) 50m\",\"b\":\"b) 120m\",\"c\":\"c) 150m\",\"d\":\"d) none of them\"},\"userAnswer\":\"a) 50m\",\"userAnswerLetter\":\"a\",\"correctAnswer\":\"d) none of them\",\"correctAnswerLetter\":\"d\",\"isCorrect\":false,\"points\":0,\"questionImgUrl\":\"\"},{\"questionId\":\"9_q8\",\"questionText\":\"A fastening can only be used in cases of circumstances outside one’s control and exclusively for pulling a vehicle all the way to the place of repair at a speed which in any case cannot exceed 20km per hour. These fastenings must be shown in the following manner:\",\"options\":{\"a\":\"a) a red piece of cloth measuring a minimum 0.50m by side\",\"b\":\"b) an orange colored light laterally visible\",\"c\":\"c) a square white panel of at least 0.30m by side\",\"d\":\"d) none these\"},\"userAnswer\":\"a) a red piece of cloth measuring a minimum 0.50m by side\",\"userAnswerLetter\":\"a\",\"correctAnswer\":\"c) a square white panel of at least 0.30m by side\",\"correctAnswerLetter\":\"c\",\"isCorrect\":false,\"points\":0,\"questionImgUrl\":\"\"},{\"questionId\":\"9_q9\",\"questionText\":\"Except in urban areas, on the other roads as determined by the minister having transports in his duties, the maximum weight authorized by articulated vehicles with three axle is:\",\"options\":{\"a\":\"a) 12 tones\",\"b\":\"b) 16 tones\",\"c\":\"c) 10 tones\",\"d\":\"d) none of the answers is correct\"},\"userAnswer\":\"a) 12 tones\",\"userAnswerLetter\":\"a\",\"correctAnswer\":\"a) 12 tones\",\"correctAnswerLetter\":\"a\",\"isCorrect\":true,\"points\":1,\"questionImgUrl\":\"\"}]'),
