ning triangle?\",\"options\":{\"a\":\"a. 5 meters\",\"b\":\"b. 25 meters\",\"c\":\"c. 45 meters\",\"d\":\"d. 100 meters\"},\"userAnswer\":\"a. 5 meters\",\"userAnswerLetter\":\"a\",\"correctAnswer\":\"b. 25 meters\",\"correctAnswerLetter\":\"b\",\"isCorrect\":false,\"points\":0,\"questionImgUrl\":\"/uploads/question-images/q268.png\"},{\"questionId\":\"12_q19\",\"questionText\":\"Whoever pushes a motorcycle by hand must be considered as:\",\"options\":{\"a\":\"a. Pedestrian\",\"b\":\"b. Driver\",\"c\":\"c. Passenger\",\"d\":\"d. A and B are correct\"},\"userAnswer\":\"a. Pedestrian\",\"userAnswerLetter\":\"a\",\"correctAnswer\":\"b. Driver\",\"correctAnswerLetter\":\"b\",\"isCorrect\":false,\"points\":0,\"questionImgUrl\":\"/uploads/question-images/q269.png\"},{\"questionId\":\"12_q2\",\"questionText\":\"What does this sign mean?\",\"options\":{\"a\":\"a. Turn left for parking area\",\"b\":\"b. No through road\",\"c\":\"c. No entry for traffic turning left\",\"d\":\"d. Turn left for ferry terminal\"},\"userAnswer\":\"a. Turn left for parking area\",\"userAnswerLetter\":\"a\",\"correctAnswer\":\"b. No through road\",\"correctAnswerLetter\":\"b\",\"isCorrect\":false,\"points\":0,\"questionImgUrl\":\"/uploads/question-images/q252.png\"},{\"questionId\":\"12_q20\",\"questionText\":\"Triangular Shape road signs announce:\",\"options\":{\"a\":\"a. Danger\",\"b\":\"b. Prohibition\",\"c\":\"c. Obligation\",\"d\":\"d. None of the answers is correct\"},\"userAnswer\":\"b. Prohibition\",\"userAnswerLetter\":\"b\",\"correctAnswer\":\"a. Danger\",\"correctAnswerLetter\":\"a\",\"isCorrect\":false,\"points\":0,\"questionImgUrl\":\"/uploads/question-images/q270.png\"},{\"questionId\":\"12_q3\",\"questionText\":\"What does a red traffic light mean?\",\"options\":{\"a\":\"a. You stop unless turning left\",\"b\":\"b. Stop, if you’re able to brake safely\",\"c\":\"c. Prohibition to move beyond the signal\",\"d\":\"d. Go if your exit from the junction is blocked\"},\"userAnswer\":\"a. You stop unless turning left\",\"userAnswerLetter\":\"a\",\"correctAnswer\":\"c. Prohibition to move beyond the signal\",\"correctAnswerLetter\":\"c\",\"isCorrect\":false,\"points\":0,\"questionImgUrl\":\"/uploads/question-images/q253.png\"},{\"questionId\":\"12_q4\",\"questionText\":\"What does a yellow light mean?\",\"options\":{\"a\":\"a. Prepare to go\",\"b\":\"b. Prohibition to move beyond the stop line or, in default of any stop line, the signal itself\",\"c\":\"c. A and B are correct\",\"d\":\"d. None of the answers is correct\"},\"userAnswer\":\"a. Prepare to go\",\"userAnswerLetter\":\"a\",\"correctAnswer\":\"b. Prohibition to move beyond the stop line or, in default of any stop line, the signal itself\",\"correctAnswerLetter\":\"b\",\"isCorrect\":false,\"points\":0,\"questionImgUrl\":\"/uploads/question-images/q254.png\"},{\"questionId\":\"12_q5\",\"questionText\":\"What does a green light mean?\",\"options\":{\"a\":\"a. Prepare to go\",\"b\":\"b. Authorization to pass the signal\",\"c\":\"c. Stop if your exit from the junction is blocked\",\"d\":\"d. None of the answers is correct\"},\"userAnswer\":\"a. Prepare to go\",\"userAnswerLetter\":\"a\",\"correctAnswer\":\"b. Authorization to pass the signal\",\"correctAnswerLetter\":\"b\",\"isCorrect\":false,\"points\":0,\"questionImgUrl\":\"/uploads/question-images/q255.png\"},{\"questionId\":\"12_q6\",\"questionText\":\"What does this broken white line mean?\",\"options\":{\"a\":\"a. It’s forbidden to cross this line\",\"b\":\"b. No stopping allowed\",\"c\":\"c. You’re approaching a hazard\",\"d\":\"d. No overtaking allowed\"},\"userAnswer\":\"a. It’s forbidden to cross this line\",\"userAnswerLetter\":\"a\",\"correctAnswer\":\"a. It’s forbidden to cross this line\",\"correctAnswerLetter\":\"a\",\"isCorrect\":true,\"points\":1,\"questionImgUrl\":\"/uploads/question-images/q256.png\"},{\"questionId\":\"12_q7\",\"questionText\":\"What does this sign mean?\",\"options\":{\"a\":\"a. Two-way traffic\",\"b\":\"b. Two-way traffic straight ahead\",\"c\":\"c. Showing an area where cyclists are supposed to enter\",\"d\":\"d. None of the answers is correct\"},\"userAnswer\":\"a. Two-way traffic\",\"userAnswerLetter\":\"a\",\"correctAnswer\":\"a. Two-way traffic\",\"correctAnswerLetter\":\"a\",\"isCorrect\":true,\"points\":1,\"questionImgUrl\":\"/uploads/question-images/q257.png\"},{\"questionId\":\"12_q8\",\"questionText\":\"What does this sign mean?\",\"options\":{\"a\":\"a. Service area 30 miles ahead\",\"b\":\"b. Maximum speed 30km/h\",\"c\":\"c. Minimum speed 30 km/h\",\"d\":\"d. Lay-by 30 miles ahead\"},\"userAnswer\":\"a. Service area 30 miles ahead\",\"userAnswerLetter\":\"a\",\"correctAnswer\":\"c. Minimum speed 30 km/h\",\"correctAnswerLetter\":\"c\",\"isCorrect\":false,\"points\":0,\"questionImgUrl\":\"/uploads/question-images/q258.png\"},{\"questionId\":\"12_q9\",\"questionText\":\"What does this sign mean?\",\"options\":{\"a\":\"a. Slippery road ahead\",\"b\":\"b. Tires liable to punctures ahead\",\"c\":\"c. Approaching a danger but undefined danger\",\"d\":\"d. Service area ahead\"},\"userAnswer\":\"a. Slippery road ahead\",\"userAnswerLetter\":\"a\",\"correctAnswer\":\"c. Approaching a danger but undefined danger\",\"correctAnswerLetter\":\"c\",\"isCorrect\":false,\"points\":0,\"questionImgUrl\":\"/uploads/question-images/q259.png\"}]'),
('b32de36c-d20b-4f94-ab46-2551be11c6d9', '6ce8cf6f-e9bd-42b5-9cc6-bda9fe1f1e05', '10', 20, 20, 4, 188, '{\"10_q1\":\"d) B and c are correct answers\",\"10_q10\":\"a. Sound your horn as you pass\",\"10_q11\":\"a. Look in the nearside mirror\",\"10_q12\":\"e. Brake harshly and stop well out into the road\",\"10_q13\":\"b. To give a better view into the road that you’re joining\",\"10_q14\":\"b. Drive on, keeping to the right\",\"10_q15\":\"a. Give way to the elderly and infirm only\",\"10_q16\":\"a.\",\"10_q17\":\"d. Rear fog lights\",\"10_q18\":\"b. You’ll be dazzled by other headlights\",\"10_q19\":\"c. Leave dipped headlights switched on\",\"10_q2\":\"d) B and c are correct answers\",\"10_q20\":\"a. Minimum speed 30km/h\",\"10_q3\":\"c) A and B are correct\",\"10_q4\":\"d) When approaching a dip in the road\",\"10_q5\":\"b. Maintain speed\",\"10_q6\":\"a. You’ll allow the driver to see you in their mirrors\",\"10_q7\":\"a. Stop and then move forward slowly and carefully for a clear view\",\"10_q8\":\"a. Play some loud music\",\"10_q9\":\"a. To make your dials easier to see\"}', 0, '2025-09-25 19:34:50', 0, '2025-09-25 19:34:50', '2025-09-25 19:34:50', '[{\"questionId\":\"10_q1\",\"questionText\":\"Your mobile phone rings while you are travelling. What should you do?\",\"options\":{\"a\":\"a) Respond or stop immediately\",\"b\":\"b) Ignore It\",\"c\":\"c) Pull up at the nearest kerb and answer the phone call.\",\"d\":\"d) B and c are correct answers\"},\"userAnswer\":\"d) B and c are correct answers\",\"userAnswerLetter\":\"d\",\"correctAnswer\":\"c) Pull up at the nearest kerb and answer the phone call.\",\"correctAnswerLetter\":\"c\",\"isCorrect\":false,\"points\":0,\"questionImgUrl\":null},{\"questionId\":\"10_q10\",\"questionText\":\"You’re travelling a public highway. How should you pass the cyclist?\",\"options\":{\"a\":\"a. Sound your horn as you pass\",\"b\":\"b. Keep close to them as you pass\",\"c\":\"c. Leave adequate space as you pass\",\"d\":\"d. Change down one gear before you pass\"},\"userAnswer\":\"a. Sound your horn as you pass\",\"userAnswerLetter\":\"a\",\"correctAnswer\":\"c. Leave adequate space as you pass\",\"correctAnswerLetter\":\"c\",\"isCorrect\":false,\"points\":0,\"questionImgUrl\":null},{\"questionId\":\"10_q11\",\"questionText\":\"You can’t see clearly behind when reversing. What should you do?\",\"options\":{\"a\":\"a. Look in the nearside mirror\",\"b\":\"b. Open the window to look behind\",\"c\":\"c. Open the door to look behind\",\"d\":\"d. Ask someone to guide you\"},\"userAnswer\":\"a. Look in the nearside mirror\",\"userAnswerLetter\":\"a\",\"correctAnswer\":\"a. Look in the nearside mirror\",\"correctAnswerLetter\":\"a\",\"isCorrect\":true,\"points\":1,\"questionImgUrl\":null},{\"questionId\":\"10_q12\",\"questionText\":\"You’re being followed by an ambulance showing flashing lights. What should you do?\",\"options\":{\"a\":\"a. Pull over as soon as it’s safe to do so\",\"b\":\"b. Accelerate hard to get away from it\",\"c\":\"d. Maintain your speed and course\",\"d\":\"e. Brake harshly and stop well out into the road\"},\"userAnswer\":\"e. Brake harshly and stop well out into the road\",\"userAnswerLetter\":\"e\",\"correctAnswer\":\"a. Pull over as soon as it’s safe to do so\",\"correctAnswerLetter\":\"a\",\"isCorrect\":false,\"points\":0,\"questionImgUrl\":null},{\"questionId\":\"10_q13\",\"questionText\":\"You wish to turn left ahead. Why should you take up the correct position in good time?\",\"options\":{\"a\":\"a. To allow other drivers to pull out in front of you\",\"b\":\"b. To give a better view into the road that you’re joining\",\"c\":\"c. To help other road users know what you intend to do\",\"d\":\"d. To allow drivers to pass you on the left\"},\"userAnswer\":\"b. To give a better view into the road that you’re joining\",\"userAnswerLetter\":\"b\",\"correctAnswer\":\"d. To allow drivers to pass you on the left\",\"correctAnswerLetter\":\"d\",\"isCorrect\":false,\"points\":0,\"questionImgUrl\":null},{\"questionId\":\"10_q14\",\"questionText\":\"You’re driving behind a trailer. What should you do if it signals right but you are heading to the left?\",\"options\":{\"a\":\"a. Slow down and let the trailer turn\",\"b\":\"b. Drive on, keeping to the right\",\"c\":\"c. Overtake on the right of it\",\"d\":\"d. Hold your speed and sound your horn\"},\"userAnswer\":\"b. Drive on, keeping to the right\",\"userAnswerLetter\":\"b\",\"correctAnswer\":\"a. Slow down and let the trailer turn\",\"correctAnswerLetter\":\"a\",\"isCorrect\":false,\"points\":0,\"questionImgUrl\":null},{\"questionId\":\"10_q15\",\"questionText\":\"You’re approaching a zebra crossing. Pedestrians are waiting to cross. What should you do?\",\"options\":{\"a\":\"a. Give way to the elderly and infirm only\",\"b\":\"b. Slow down and prepare to stop\",\"c\":\"c. Use your headlights to indicate they can cross\",\"d\":\"d. Wave at them to cross the road\"},\"userAnswer\":\"a. Give way to the elderly and infirm only\",\"userAnswerLetter\":\"a\",\"correctAnswer\":\"b. Slow down and prepare to stop\",\"correctAnswerLetter\":\"b\",\"isCorrect\":false,\"points\":0,\"questionImgUrl\":null},{\"questionId\":\"10_q16\",\"questionText\":\"You’re about to overtake a slow-moving motorcyclist. Which one of these signs would make you take special care?\",\"options\":{\"a\":\"a.\",\"b\":\"b.\",\"c\":\"c.\",\"d\":\"d.\"},\"userAnswer\":\"a.\",\"userAnswerLetter\":\"a\",\"correctAnswer\":\"c.\",\"correctAnswerLetter\":\"c\",\"isCorrect\":false,\"points\":0,\"questionImgUrl\":\"assets/examimages/q224.png\"},{\"questionId\":\"10_q17\",\"questionText\":\"Daytime visibility is poor but not seriously reduced. Which lights must be switched on?\",\"options\":{\"a\":\"a. Headlight and fog lights\",\"b\":\"b. Front fog lights\",\"c\":\"c. Dipped headlights\",\"d\":\"d. Rear fog lights\"},\"userAnswer\":\"d. Rear fog lights\",\"userAnswerLetter\":\"d\",\"correctAnswer\":\"b. Front fog lights\",\"correctAnswerLetter\":\"b\",\"isCorrect\":false,\"points\":0,\"questionImgUrl\":null},{\"questionId\":\"10_q18\",\"questionText\":\"Why should you always reduce your speed when travelling in fog?\",\"options\":{\"a\":\"a. The brakes don’t work as well\",\"b\":\"b. You’ll be dazzled by other headlights\",\"c\":\"c. It’s more difficult to see what’s ahead\",\"d\":\"d. The engine will take longer to warm up\"},\"userAnswer\":\"b. You’ll be dazzled by other headlights\",\"userAnswerLetter\":\"b\",\"correctAnswer\":\"c. It’s more difficult to see what’s ahead\",\"correctAnswerLetter\":\"c\",\"isCorrect\":false,\"points\":0,\"questionImgUrl\":null},{\"questionId\":\"10_q19\",\"questionText\":\"What should you do if you park on the road when it’s foggy?\",\"options\":{\"a\":\"a. Leave sidelights switched on\",\"b\":\"b. Leave dipped headlights and fog lights switched on\",\"c\":\"c. Leave dipped headlights switched on\",\"d\":\"d. Leave main-beam headlights switched on\"},\"userAnswer\":\"c. Leave dipped headlights switched on\",\"userAnswerLetter\":\"c\",\"correctAnswer\":\"a. Leave sidelights switched on\",\"correctAnswerLetter\":\"a\",\"isCorrect\":false,\"points\":0,\"questionImgUrl\":null},{\"questionId\":\"10_q2\",\"questionText\":\"Your mobile phone rings while you are travelling. What should you do?\",\"options\":{\"a\":\"a) Respond or stop immediately\",\"b\":\"b) Ignore It\",\"c\":\"c) Pull up at the nearest kerb and answer the phone call.\",\"d\":\"d) B and c are correct answers\"},\"userAnswer\":\"d) B and c are correct answers\",\"userAnswerLetter\":\"d\",\"correctAnswer\":\"c) Pull up at the nearest kerb and answer the phone call.\",\"correctAnswerLetter\":\"c\",\"isCorrect\":false,\"points\":0,\"questionImgUrl\":null},{\"questionId\":\"10_q20\",\"questionText\":\"What does this sign mean?\",\"options\":{\"a\":\"a. Minimum speed 30km/h\",\"b\":\"b. End of compulsory maximum speed\",\"c\":\"c. End of minimum speed\",\"d\":\"d. Maximum speed 30km/h\"},\"userAnswer\":\"a. Minimum speed 30km/h\",\"userAnswerLetter\":\"a\",\"correctAnswer\":\"b. End of compulsory maximum speed\",\"correctAnswerLetter\":\"b\",\"isCorrect\":false,\"points\":0,\"questionImgUrl\":\"assets/examimages/q229.png\"},{\"questionId\":\"10_q3\",\"questionText\":\"What should you do before making a U-turn?\",\"options\":{\"a\":\"a) Give arm signal as well as using your indicators\",\"b\":\"b) Check signal to see that U-turns are permitted\",\"c\":\"c) A and B are correct\",\"d\":\"d) None of the answers is correct\"},\"userAnswer\":\"c) A and B are correct\",\"userAnswerLetter\":\"c\",\"correctAnswer\":\"c) A and B are correct\",\"correctAnswerLetter\":\"c\",\"isCorrect\":true,\"points\":1,\"questionImgUrl\":null},{\"questionId\":\"10_q4\",\"questionText\":\"In which of these situations should you avoid overtaking?\",\"options\":{\"a\":\"a) Just after a bend and wait for a safer place to pull out\",\"b\":\"b) In a one-way street\",\"c\":\"c) On a 30 km/h road\",\"d\":\"d) When approaching a dip in the road\"},\"userAnswer\":\"d) When approaching a dip in the road\",\"userAnswerLetter\":\"d\",\"correctAnswer\":\"a) Just after a bend and wait for a safer place to pull out\",\"correctAnswerLetter\":\"a\",\"isCorrect\":false,\"points\":0,\"questionImgUrl\":null},{\"questionId\":\"10_q5\",\"questionText\":\"What should you do when you’re approaching traffic lights that have been on yellow color?\",\"options\":{\"a\":\"a. Accelerate hard\",\"b\":\"b. Maintain speed\",\"c\":\"c) Be ready to stop\",\"d\":\"d. Brake hard\"},\"userAnswer\":\"b. Maintain speed\",\"userAnswerLetter\":\"b\",\"correctAnswer\":\"c) Be ready to stop\",\"correctAnswerLetter\":\"c\",\"isCorrect\":false,\"points\":0,\"questionImgUrl\":\"assets/examimages/q214.png\"},{\"questionId\":\"10_q6\",\"questionText\":\"You’re following a trailer. Why should you stay at a safe distance behind it?\",\"options\":{\"a\":\"a. You’ll allow the driver to see you in their mirrors\",\"b\":\"b. You’ll be able to corner more quickly\",\"c\":\"c. You’ll help the large vehicle to stop more easily\",\"d\":\"d. You’ll keep out of the wind better\"},\"userAnswer\":\"a. You’ll allow the driver to see you in their mirrors\",\"userAnswerLetter\":\"a\",\"correctAnswer\":\"a. You’ll allow the driver to see you in their mirrors\",\"correctAnswerLetter\":\"a\",\"isCorrect\":true,\"points\":1,\"questionImgUrl\":null},{\"questionId\":\"10_q7\",\"questionText\":\"You’re waiting to turn right at the end of a road. Your view is obstructed by stopped vehicles. What should you do?\",\"options\":{\"a\":\"a. Stop and then move forward slowly and carefully for a clear view\",\"b\":\"b. Move quickly to where you can see so you block traffic from one direction\",\"c\":\"c. Wait for pedestrians to let you know when it’s safe for you to emerge\",\"d\":\"d. Turn your vehicle around immediately and find another junction to use\"},\"userAnswer\":\"a. Stop and then move forward slowly and carefully for a clear view\",\"userAnswerLetter\":\"a\",\"correctAnswer\":\"a. Stop and then move forward slowly and carefully for a clear view\",\"correctAnswerLetter\":\"a\",\"isCorrect\":true,\"points\":1,\"questionImgUrl\":null},{\"questionId\":\"10_q8\",\"questionText\":\"You’re on a long motorway journey. What should you do if you start to feel sleepy?\",\"options\":{\"a\":\"a. Play some loud music\",\"b\":\"b. Drive faster to complete your journey sooner\",\"c\":\"c. Leave the motorway and stop in a safe place\",\"d\":\"d. None of the answers is correct\"},\"userAnswer\":\"a. Play some loud music\",\"userAnswerLetter\":\"a\",\"correctAnswer\":\"c. Leave the motorway and stop in a safe place\",\"correctAnswerLetter\":\"c\",\"isCorrect\":false,\"points\":0,\"questionImgUrl\":null},{\"questionId\":\"10_q9\",\"questionText\":\"Why should you switch your lights on when it first starts to get dark?\",\"options\":{\"a\":\"a. To make your dials easier to see\",\"b\":\"b. So others can see you more easily\",\"c\":\"c. So that you blend in with other drivers\",\"d\":\"d. Because the street lights are lit\"},\"userAnswer\":\"a. To make your dials easier to see\",\"userAnswerLetter\":\"a\",\"correctAnswer\":\"b. So others can see you more easily\",\"correctAnswerLetter\":\"b\",\"isCorrect\":false,\"points\":0,\"questionImgUrl\":null}]'),
